39 *** Types
40 ***/

42/*%
43 * A simple database. This is an opaque type.
44 */
45typedef struct dns_sdb dns_sdb_t;
46
47/*%
48 * A simple database lookup in progress. This is an opaque type.
49 */
50typedef struct dns_sdblookup dns_sdblookup_t;
51
52/*%
53 * A simple database traversal in progress. This is an opaque type.
54 */
55typedef struct dns_sdballnodes dns_sdballnodes_t;
56
57typedef isc_result_t
58(*dns_sdblookupfunc_t)(const char *zone, const char *name, void *dbdata,
59 dns_sdblookup_t *lookup,
60 dns_clientinfomethods_t *methods,
61 dns_clientinfo_t *clientinfo);
62typedef isc_result_t
63(*dns_sdblookup2func_t)(const dns_name_t *zone, const dns_name_t *name,
64 void *dbdata, dns_sdblookup_t *lookup,
65 dns_clientinfomethods_t *methods,
66 dns_clientinfo_t *clientinfo);
67
68typedef isc_result_t
69(*dns_sdbauthorityfunc_t)(const char *zone, void *dbdata, dns_sdblookup_t *);
70
71typedef isc_result_t
72(*dns_sdballnodesfunc_t)(const char *zone, void *dbdata,
73 dns_sdballnodes_t *allnodes);
74
75typedef isc_result_t
76(*dns_sdbcreatefunc_t)(const char *zone, int argc, char **argv,
77 void *driverdata, void **dbdata);
78
79typedef void
80(*dns_sdbdestroyfunc_t)(const char *zone, void *driverdata, void **dbdata);
81
82
83typedef struct dns_sdbmethods {
84 dns_sdblookupfunc_t lookup;
85 dns_sdbauthorityfunc_t authority;
86 dns_sdballnodesfunc_t allnodes;
87 dns_sdbcreatefunc_t create;
88 dns_sdbdestroyfunc_t destroy;
89 dns_sdblookup2func_t lookup2;
90} dns_sdbmethods_t;

92/***
93 *** Functions
94 ***/
95
96ISC_LANG_BEGINDECLS
97
98#define DNS_SDBFLAG_RELATIVEOWNER 0x00000001U
99#define DNS_SDBFLAG_RELATIVERDATA 0x00000002U
100#define DNS_SDBFLAG_THREADSAFE 0x00000004U
101#define DNS_SDBFLAG_DNS64 0x00000008U
102
103isc_result_t
104dns_sdb_register(const char *drivername, const dns_sdbmethods_t *methods,
105 void *driverdata, unsigned int flags, isc_mem_t *mctx,
106 dns_sdbimplementation_t **sdbimp);
107/*%<
108 * Register a simple database driver for the database type 'drivername',
109 * implemented by the functions in '*methods'.
110 *
111 * sdbimp must point to a NULL dns_sdbimplementation_t pointer. That is,
112 * sdbimp != NULL && *sdbimp == NULL. It will be assigned a value that
113 * will later be used to identify the driver when deregistering it.
114 *
115 * The name server will perform lookups in the database by calling the
116 * function 'lookup', passing it a printable zone name 'zone', a printable
117 * domain name 'name', and a copy of the argument 'dbdata' that
118 * was potentially returned by the create function. The 'dns_sdblookup_t'
119 * argument to 'lookup' and 'authority' is an opaque pointer to be passed to
120 * ns_sdb_putrr().
121 *
122 * The lookup function returns the lookup results to the name server
123 * by calling ns_sdb_putrr() once for each record found. On success,
124 * the return value of the lookup function should be ISC_R_SUCCESS.
125 * If the domain name 'name' does not exist, the lookup function should
126 * ISC_R_NOTFOUND. Any other return value is treated as an error.
127 *
128 * Lookups at the zone apex will cause the server to also call the
129 * function 'authority' (if non-NULL), which must provide an SOA record
130 * and NS records for the zone by calling ns_sdb_putrr() once for each of
131 * these records. The 'authority' function may be NULL if invoking
132 * the 'lookup' function on the zone apex will return SOA and NS records.
133 *
134 * The allnodes function, if non-NULL, fills in an opaque structure to be
135 * used by a database iterator. This allows the zone to be transferred.
136 * This may use a considerable amount of memory for large zones, and the
137 * zone transfer may not be fully RFC1035 compliant if the zone is
138 * frequently changed.
139 *
140 * The create function will be called for each zone configured
141 * into the name server using this database type. It can be used
142 * to create a "database object" containing zone specific data,
143 * which can make use of the database arguments specified in the
144 * name server configuration.
145 *
146 * The destroy function will be called to free the database object
147 * when its zone is destroyed.
148 *
149 * The create and destroy functions may be NULL.
150 *
151 * If flags includes DNS_SDBFLAG_RELATIVEOWNER, the lookup and authority
152 * functions will be called with relative names rather than absolute names.
153 * The string "@" represents the zone apex in this case.
154 *
155 * If flags includes DNS_SDBFLAG_RELATIVERDATA, the rdata strings may
156 * include relative names. Otherwise, all names in the rdata string must
157 * be absolute. Be aware that if relative names are allowed, any
158 * absolute names must contain a trailing dot.
159 *
160 * If flags includes DNS_SDBFLAG_THREADSAFE, the driver must be able to
161 * handle multiple lookups in parallel. Otherwise, calls into the driver
162 * are serialized.
163 */
164
165void
166dns_sdb_unregister(dns_sdbimplementation_t **sdbimp);
167/*%<
168 * Removes the simple database driver from the list of registered database
169 * types. There must be no active databases of this type when this function
170 * is called.
171 */
172
173/*% See dns_sdb_putradata() */
174isc_result_t
175dns_sdb_putrr(dns_sdblookup_t *lookup, const char *type, dns_ttl_t ttl,
176 const char *data);
177isc_result_t
178dns_sdb_putrdata(dns_sdblookup_t *lookup, dns_rdatatype_t type, dns_ttl_t ttl,
179 const unsigned char *rdata, unsigned int rdlen);
180/*%<
181 * Add a single resource record to the lookup structure to be
182 * returned in the query response. dns_sdb_putrr() takes the
183 * resource record in master file text format as a null-terminated
184 * string, and dns_sdb_putrdata() takes the raw RDATA in
185 * uncompressed wire format.
186 */
187
188/*% See dns_sdb_putnamerdata() */
189isc_result_t
190dns_sdb_putnamedrr(dns_sdballnodes_t *allnodes, const char *name,
191 const char *type, dns_ttl_t ttl, const char *data);
192isc_result_t
193dns_sdb_putnamedrdata(dns_sdballnodes_t *allnodes, const char *name,
194 dns_rdatatype_t type, dns_ttl_t ttl,
195 const void *rdata, unsigned int rdlen);
196/*%<
197 * Add a single resource record to the allnodes structure to be
198 * included in a zone transfer response, in text or wire
199 * format as above.
200 */
201
202isc_result_t
203dns_sdb_putsoa(dns_sdblookup_t *lookup, const char *mname, const char *rname,
204 uint32_t serial);
205/*%<
206 * This function may optionally be called from the 'authority' callback
207 * to simplify construction of the SOA record for 'zone'. It will
208 * provide a SOA listing 'mname' as as the master server and 'rname' as
209 * the responsible person mailbox. It is the responsibility of the
210 * driver to increment the serial number between responses if necessary.
211 * All other SOA fields will have reasonable default values.
212 */
213
214ISC_LANG_ENDDECLS

216#endif /* DNS_SDB_H */
